			  Let \(F\) be the function whose graph is shown below.
  Evaluate each of the following expressions.
  \par 
{\it (If a limit does not exist or is undefined, enter \lq\lq{}DNE\rq\rq{}.)} 
  \par 

\par\medskip\hbox{\qquad\vtop{\advance\hsize by -3em 
\par\begin{tabular}{rrcl}
1.\ &\(\displaystyle\lim_{x\to -1^-} F(x)\)&=&\ \mbox{\parbox[t]{3ex}{\hrulefill}}\\ \noalign{\kern 0pt}
2.\ &\(\displaystyle\lim_{x\to -1^+} F(x)\)&=&\ \mbox{\parbox[t]{3ex}{\hrulefill}}\\ \noalign{\kern 0pt}
3.\ &\(\displaystyle\lim_{x\to -1} F(x)\)&=&\ \mbox{\parbox[t]{3ex}{\hrulefill}}\\ \noalign{\kern 0pt}
4.\ &\(F(-1)\)&=&\ \mbox{\parbox[t]{3ex}{\hrulefill}}\\ \noalign{\kern 0pt}
5.\ &\(\displaystyle\lim_{x\to 1^-} F(x)\)&=&\ \mbox{\parbox[t]{3ex}{\hrulefill}}\\ \noalign{\kern 0pt}
6.\ &\(\displaystyle\lim_{x\to 1^+} F(x)\)&=&\ \mbox{\parbox[t]{3ex}{\hrulefill}}\\ \noalign{\kern 0pt}
7.\ &\(\displaystyle\lim_{x\to 1} F(x)\)&=&\ \mbox{\parbox[t]{3ex}{\hrulefill}}\\ \noalign{\kern 0pt}
8.\ &\(\displaystyle\lim_{x \to 3} F(x)\)&=&\ \mbox{\parbox[t]{3ex}{\hrulefill}}\\ \noalign{\kern 0pt}
9.\ &\(F(3)\)&=&\ \mbox{\parbox[t]{3ex}{\hrulefill}}\\ \noalign{\kern 0pt}
\end{tabular}
